I really like the tree-like logging that we have with `git-deps status`

┌─ deps/domish
├─ dep      ✓ [SYNCED] [main] 974b594d5135737f8c1bae89d3735712fcedc33b 2025-08-29
├─ local    ✓ [SYNCED] [main] 974b594d5135737f8c1bae89d3735712fcedc33b 2025-08-29
├─ remote   ✓ [SYNCED] [main] 974b594d5135737f8c1bae89d3735712fcedc33b 2025-08-29
└

However, event when operations are scoped at an entry, the log does not appear
within the scope of the entry

⋯ Checking deps/domish...
⋯ Fetching updates (this may take a moment…)
⋯ Fetch completed successfully
✓ deps/domish updated
┌─ deps/domish
├─ dep      ✓ [SYNCED] [main] 974b594d5135737f8c1bae89d3735712fcedc33b 2025-08-29
├─ local    ✓ [SYNCED] [main] 974b594d5135737f8c1bae89d3735712fcedc33b 2025-08-29
├─ remote   ✓ [SYNCED] [main] 974b594d5135737f8c1bae89d3735712fcedc33b 2025-08-29
└─
 … Status check completed

It would be better to have

┌─ deps/domish
├⋯ Fetching updates… ✓ (done)
├─ dep      ✓ [SYNCED] [main] 974b594d5135737f8c1bae89d3735712fcedc33b 2025-08-29
├─ local    ✓ [SYNCED] [main] 974b594d5135737f8c1bae89d3735712fcedc33b 2025-08-29
├─ remote   ✓ [SYNCED] [main] 974b594d5135737f8c1bae89d3735712fcedc33b 2025-08-29
└─ ✓ [SYNCED]
